s_card card-border"><div class="round_shadow"><img height="90" loading="lazy" width="90" src="https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/627a84f19cfe42b2c96f2416/63911c91a5120de49f13d23c_SC_Logo_Master_Brand.png" alt="" class="image-66"/></div><div><h2 class="heading-52">As the cloud evolves, CISOs rely on the service mesh to secure their Kubernetes projects </h2><p class="paragraph-61">December 6, 2022</p><p class="news_p">The fast-paced Kubernetes ecosystem has given rise to multiple tools and concepts that have transformed how organizations deploy and operate applications in cloud environments.</p></div></div></a></div><div role="listitem" class="w-dyn-item"><a href="https://thenewstack.io/service-mesh-demand-for-kubernetes-shifts-to-security/" target="_blank" class="w-inline-block"><div class="news_card card-border"><div class="round_shadow"><img height="90" loading="lazy" width="90" src="https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/627a84f19cfe42b2c96f2416/6296343bdb332d72d2774ccd_the-new-stack.png" alt="" class="image-66"/></div><div><h2 class="heading-52">Service Mesh Demand for Kubernetes Shifts to Security</h2><p class="paragraph-61">October 27, 2022</p><p class="news_p">Service mesh has long been considered an essential staple in creating, deploying and managing Kubernetes environments. However, as the community becomes more aware of the threats and challenges associated with managing highly distributed containerized environments, security has emerged as the main benefit of what service mesh offers DevOps teams.</p></div></div></a></div><div role="listitem" class="w-dyn-item"><a href="https://containerjournal.com/features/buoyant-updates-linkerd-to-simplify-zero-trust-security/" target="_blank" class="w-inline-block"><div class="news_card card-border"><div class="round_shadow"><img height="90" loading="lazy" width="90" src="https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/627a84f19cfe42b2c96f2416/629636fa84f0b088abd946a7_11ofcuc.png" alt="" class="image-66"/></div><div><h2 class="heading-52">Buoyant Updates Linkerd to Simplify Zero-Trust Security</h2><p class="paragraph-61">August 24, 2022</p><p class="news_p">Buoyant today updated the open source Linkerd service mesh to add support for route-based authorization policies that enforce zero-trust policies within microsegmented Kubernetes environments. In addition, the company is adding support for the Kubernetes Gateway application programming interface (API) and access logging to produce Apache-style request logs.</p></div></div></a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="section-3 wf-section"><div class="container-14 w-container"><h2 class="h2 centeredtext">Case Studies</h2><div class="case_studies_home"><div class="collection-list-wrapper-5 w-dyn-list"><div role="list" class="collection-list-10 w-dyn-items"><div role="listitem" class="collection-item-13 w-dyn-item"><div class="card_cs"><a href="/case-studies/ingrid" class="buttontael_big w-button">READ MORE</a><p class="paragraph-3">Ingrid’s road to a service mesh: gRPC load balancing and certificate rotation</p><img height="40" loading="lazy" src="https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/627a84f19cfe42b2c96f2416/638519fd6884d968494f9b14_Ingrid.png" alt="Ingrid’s road to a service mesh: gRPC load balancing and certificate rotation" class="cs_logo"/></div></div><div role="listitem" class="collection-item-13 w-dyn-item"><div class="card_cs"><a href="/case-studies/nav" class="buttontael_big w-button">READ MORE</a><p class="paragraph-3">Changing Service Mesh: How NAV swapped Istio with Linkerd with hardly any downtime</p><img height="40" loading="lazy" src="https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/627a84f19cfe42b2c96f2416/6387e83cded593180da8d235_okNAV.png" alt="Changing Service Mesh: How NAV swapped Istio with Linkerd with hardly any downtime" sizes="(max-width: 1919px) 100vw, 4000.390625px" srcset="https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/627a84f19cfe42b2c96f2416/6387e83cded593180da8d235_okNAV-p-500.png 500w, https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/627a84f19cfe42b2c96f2416/6387e83cded593180